\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. C. stelleri} (S.G. Gmelin) Prantl,{\i  Bot. Jahrb.}{\b  3:} 413 (1882). Leaves arising singly from a slender, creeping rhizome, 8-20 × 2-5 cm wide, 2-pinnate, ovate to ovate-elongate; petiole equalling or rather longer than the lamina; ultimate segments of sterile leaves similar to those of {\b 1}, those of the fertile leaves 2-3 mm wide, linear-lanceolate. {\i Rock-crevices in shady places. N.E. Russia}. Rs(N, C). ({\i Arctic and subarctic Asia; N. America}.)
