\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. P. incompleta} Cav.,{\i  Anal. Ci. Nat.}{\b  2:} 107 (1801) ({\i P. serrulata} Forskål, non L. fil.,{\i  P. arguta} Aiton). Rhizome creeping; scales long, narrow, dark brown. Petiole up to c. 50 cm, brown; lamina up to c. 100 × 40 cm, ovate; pinnae 7-9(-11) pairs, pinnatisect, the lowest pair often forked, all pinnatisect; segments oblong-lanceolate, falcate, serrate in distal ½, acute. Sori occupying lower 1/2-2/3 of the segments, not extending to the base of the sinus; indusium prominent, thick. {\i Açores; two stations in S.W. Spain.} Az Hs [Lu].
