\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b  11.       HYMENOPHYLLACEAE}
\par   

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  Edit. †D.H. Valentine & D.M. Moore.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Plants small. Rhizome slender, extensively creeping. Lamina dark, translucent green, only 1 cell thick except on the veins. Sori gradate, marginal; indusium tubular or 2-valved, symmetrical; spores tetrahedral.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 A predominantly austral and tropical family. Delimitation of species is difficult, and the plants from Europe are held by some authors to be conspecific with those in the tropics or the southern hemisphere; as here delimited, they are believed to extend outside Europe only to Madeira and Islas Canarias.
\par

